  "text": "The dipole moment of CoTX1 resulting from its chargedistribution anisotropy is shown by an arrow on Figure 5 (B). It is directed from the centre of the molecule and oriented from the lowest to the highest positive charge density. The size of the arrow is proportional to the intensity of the anisotropy. It emerges from the molecule through a basic-rich surface (Arg 6 , Lys 10 , Lys 13 , Arg [CITATION_1] and Lys 21 ; only one acidic Asp 8 residue); the opposite face being poorly basic (Arg [CITATION_2] and Lys 28 ; and one acidic Asp 9 residue).",
